* Inversion: When ESP32 is High -> Transistor ON -> DIM pulled Low -> LED OFF. The code must account for this (0% duty cycle = Max Brightness). 5.2 Firmware Implementation for 40Hz
Standard Arduino analogWrite is often fixed at 490Hz or 980Hz. The ESP32's ledc library allows specific frequency setting. // Gamma Protocol Configuration
const int pwmFreq = 40; // 40Hz
const int pwmResolution = 8;
const int pwmChannel = 0;

void setup() {
  ledcSetup(pwmChannel, pwmFreq, pwmResolution);
  ledcAttachPin(driverPin, pwmChannel);
  // 50% Duty Cycle for therapeutic flicker
  ledcWrite(pwmChannel, 127); 
}
